        <num>CCP 2453</num>
        <heading>2453.  Motion; order; service</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2453.  Motion; order; service
On ex parte written motion of the judgment creditor, personally or through his attorney, the court shall order the judgment debtor to appear in court for examination at a time fixed by the court, not less than five days from the date of service of the motion and order on the judgment debtor or his counsel of record, and to produce any books, papers, and other documents relating to the judgment debtor's property described in the motion.</p>
        </content>
